The paper deals with the fundamental limits of biometric identification systems, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves privacy and secrecy-leakages, which are related to cyber security and privacy, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a likely sub-category as well. The use of biometric data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
